  "remarks": "Judge of the Partizanski district of Minsk. He was directly involved in the judicial repression of civil society and of the democratic opposition in 2006–2007. On 15 January 2007, he sentenced the political activist Andrei Dzmitriev to 3 days in jail. His way of conducting the trial was a clear violation of the Code of Criminal Procedure. He sustained the use of evidence and testimonies irrelevant to the accused.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}